deck: The First Earth Man on Terra, the Twin of Earth
description:
Origin

Garry Verth is a veteran FBI special agent who is surprised one day when he is contacted by Vana, a woman who proves herself to be an alien from a planet called Terra which is the twin of Earth but has remained unknown due to it being in orbit on the opposite side of the Sun.

Vana reveals that that Terra, whose population is 92% female, has far more advanced technology than Earth and have been keeping an eye on Verth’s home world since 1903 in craft most people call flying saucers, and that she has been spying on Earth for the last few years to make sure that Earth does not find out about Terra and bring its warlike ways there.

She however finds herself forced to contact him because the Soviet Union has discovered the existence of Terra and is close to getting their hands on the secret of the flying saucers and the other advanced technology of her planet.

Garry Verth uses his skills as an FBI agent to prevent this from happening and later helps ease the tension of the first meetings of the people of Earth and Terra.

Creators

Garry Verth was the lead male character of the daily newspaper comic strip Twin Earth by Oskar Lebeck & Alden McWilliams which ran from 1952, to 1963 and was reprinted in part in a few issues of Tip Top Comics from Dell, a long series of Australian comics and a collection of the series in the 1990s.
name: Garry Verth

deck: Spy from the other side of the Sun.
description:
Origin

Vana is a spy from the planet Terra, a physical twin of Earth but in orbit so that it is always hidden from its sister world and different in that its human population is 92% female, it is more advanced scientifically, and they still have dinosaurs. After spying on various Earth governments for years to make sure they do not discover the existent of Terra and bring the war like ways of Earth to her home world. She however is forced to reveal herself and Terra to an FBI agent when it looks like the Russians are close to getting their hand on Terra’s advanced science.

Vana is an accomplished scientist, spy and space pilot of the type of craft known on Earth as flying saucers.

Creators

Vana was introduced in the newspaper comic strip Twin Earths by Oskar Lebeck & Alden McWilliams that ran from late 1952 to 1963.
name: Vana of Terra

deck: A huge dragon living under Madripoor.
description:
A monolithic beast of legend situated beneath the island continent of Madripoor, This titanic thunder lizard spans about the size of Japan harboring vast mystical facilities of it's own. Acting as the new base of the entire Madripoor island as well as the mobile fortress of The Hand and it's current leader Tomi Shishido, The Gorgon.

The mutant crime lord went about a mysterious ritual that would raise this colossus from the seabed beneath the criminal haven with his temple as the pinnacle; from which he controls the creature. Tomi raised the dragon in a bid to both elevate The Hand's power and status as a global threat warrant and to conquer China; Shanghai more specifically, for the intent of making a kingdom for himself and his clan.

Madagon; aptly named by a S.H.I.E.L.D analyst has a host of odd and unique properties which include producing miniature dragon spawn for select warriors to ride upon into battle.
name: Madripoor Dragon
